commit.message: Update to neon 0.33.0.
Add support for neon 33 in configure.ac

* src/options.c, src/options.h: Add opt_keepalive to
  disable/enable persistent connections.

* src/cadaver.c (open_connection): Respect the keeaplive
  option.

* src/cadaver.c (cert_verify): Display the SHA-256 cert hash
  when possible.

- Drop bundled neon sources
- Update to use submodule neon/ in buildsystem
- update CI
Test with and without bundled neon.
Add neon as a submodule.
cadaver.1 line 155 typo

Add installation testing to CI.
Update pre-release gettext-update script.
Update gettext build infrastructure.
Tweak README and add a bug report template.

Update copyright notices.

* Makefile.in (update-copyright): New target.
0.24 release (fixes #10).
Add config.rpath since libtoolize doesn't copy it.
Drop it translation which fails msgmerge, update release script.
Prepare for 0.24 release (issue #10).
Move README to markdown.
Remove references to mailman list.

* src/commands.c (execute_cat): Be less verbose for success case,
  display errors properly for failure case.
Run checks for PRs, master is now a protected branch.
* configure.ac: Try requiring autoconf 2.69 to fix Ubuntu 18.04 build.

Merge pull request #5 from hughmcmaster/configure

Modernise configure.ac and allow cadaver to regenerate its build system from source

commit.message: intl: Fix spelling of "version" in help strings

configure.ac: Check for secure_getenv() instead of __secure_getenv()

__secure_getenv() was renamed secure_getenv()
configure.ac: Check for fcntl.h
configure.ac: Check for gettimeofday()
src/search.c: #include <ctype.h> to fix compiler warnings
configure.ac: Drop obsolete jm_PREREQ_TEMPNAME and jm_FUNC_STRFTIME macros

configure.ac, neon.m4: Enable cross-compiling with pkg-config

1. Check for pkg-config earlier.
2. Use AC_PATH_TOOL to consider any user-specified host prefix.
configure.ac: Add required AM_GNU_GETTEXT_VERSION macro
